item.title: [HADOOP-12378] Fix findbugs warnings in hadoop-tools module
item.description: There are 2 warnings in hadoop-datajoin module and 4 warnings in hadoop-ant module.
item.summary: Fix findbugs warnings in hadoop-tools module

status.description: A resolution has been taken, and it is awaiting verification by reporter. From here issues are either reopened, or are closed.

comments.comment:
Attaching a patch. This patch will fix the findbugs warnings, however, the patch removes protected fields in abstract class (The class is not annotated @Public or @Stable). Therefore if an user extends the class and relies on the fields, the user's application will fail.
Would you tell me which way is better to do?

  • Fix the warnings by removing protected fields.
  • Ignore the warnings by creating findbugs-exclude.xml.

the patch removes protected fields in abstract class

In this case, DataJoinMapperBase class is a public class which assumes to be extended. These fields are useful from MapReduce jobs, so we can say the warnings are false-positive. For the reason, we can ignore the warning here. Could you update to create findbugs-exclude.xml?

For the reason, we can ignore the warning here. Could you update to create findbugs-exclude.xml?

Thanks ozawa for your reply. I'll update the patch to ignore the warnings.
